# RealignEpic Implementation-First Guidance

RealignEpic is implementation-first because it repairs the active implementation-bearing epic that downstream milestone and execution prompts consume.

The sanctioned output is the updated `.agents/epic.md` document.

Updating that file is valid when the edit makes the existing strategic initiative safer, more accurate, more constrained, or more executable for later implementation.

Realignment is a minimal strategic patch.

It is not a replacement epic, a new initiative, an audit report, or a design exercise.

Preserve the epic identity, strategic purpose, intended capability, and any unaffected milestone roadmap content.

Only change material that the EpicPreparationAudit requires.

Audit findings may be compressed into scope, constraints, dependencies, assumptions, acceptance criteria, risks, required follow-up, and milestone boundaries when those findings affect implemented capability.

They should not be copied as standalone rationale.

Unaffected sections must not be rewritten for style, completeness, tone, or polish.

The realigned epic should become a better input to implementation planning, not a broader explanation of why realignment happened.

If a proposed change does not alter what later implementation must build, preserve, avoid, validate, or sequence, it probably does not belong in the epic.

If the audit cannot support a safe minimal patch, output the documented `# Epic Realignment Blocked` response.
